trans-unit.source: Defines the attribute that controls use to identify string properties containing URL values.
This class cannot be inherited.
The UrlPropertyAttribute attribute is an attribute applied to a control property that represents a URL.

In addition to marking a string property as representing a URL, the UrlPropertyAttribute attribute defines the <xref:System.Web.UI.UrlPropertyAttribute.Filter%2A> property that identifies specific file types that can be used to filter against the property.
Initializes a new default instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.UrlPropertyAttribute"></xref> class.
A default instance of the <xref:System.Web.UI.UrlPropertyAttribute> class is initialized with the <xref:System.Web.UI.UrlPropertyAttribute.Filter%2A> property set to the value "*.\*".
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.UrlPropertyAttribute"></xref> class, setting the <xref:System.Web.UI.UrlPropertyAttribute.Filter*> property to the specified string.
An instance of a <xref:System.Web.UI.UrlPropertyAttribute> class created with this constructor is initialized with the <xref:System.Web.UI.UrlPropertyAttribute.Filter%2A> property set to `filter`.
A file filter associated with the URL-specific property.
Returns a value that indicates whether this instance is equal to a specified object.
An <xref:System.Object> to compare with this instance or a null reference (<xref uid="langword_csharp_Nothing" name="Nothing" href=""></xref> in Visual Basic).
if obj equals the type and value of this instance; otherwise, .
Gets a file filter associated with the URL-specific property.
A designer provides a filter in file selectors based on the <xref:System.Web.UI.UrlPropertyAttribute> attribute.
By default, it is initialized to "*.\*", which specifies all files with a file extension.
You can set the filter for more specific file types; for example, the filter "\*.aspx" indicates that only ASP.NET files are represented by the URL-specific property.
A file filter associated with the URL-specific property.
The default is "*.\*".
Returns the hash code for this instance.
A 32-bit signed integer hash code.
